        <h1>Travel to Hawaii</h1>
        
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/85/Sunset_next_to_Waikiki_Beach%2C_Oahu%2C_Hawai%2C_USA1.jpg" width="400" alt="Image of Sunset on Waikiki Beach">
        <h6>Image of sunset on Waikiki Beach</h6>
        
        <h2 class="heading-above-list-one">Basic Info</h2>
        
        <p><strong>Hawaii is a very popular vacation destination located in oceania (although it is part of the U.S.A.). Hawaii has a warm, humid climate, typical for tropical regions. This state is known for it's beaches, palm trees and luaus.</strong></p>
        
        <h2 class="heading-above-list-one">The Islands</h2>
        
        <p><strong>Many people assume that "Hawaii" is the name for all of the Hawaiian islands. However, this is for from the truth. The <em>state</em> of Hawaii is composed of eight islands:</strong></p>
        
        <ul>
            <li id="one">Hawaiʻi</li>
            <li id="two">Maui</li>
            <li id="three">O'ahu</li>
            <li id="four">Kaua'i</li>
            <li id="five">Moloka'i</li>
            <li id="six">Lānaʻi</li>
            <li id="seven">Niʻihau</li>
            <li id="eight">Kahoʻolawe</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h6>(The islands' nicknames are "The Big Island", "The Valley Isle", "The Gathering Place", "The Garden Isle", "The Friendly Isle", "The Pineapple Isle", "The Forbidden Isle", and "The Target Isle", respectively.) </h6>
        
        <p><strong>Each island has beautiful coastlines, great food, unique activities, and much more.</strong></p>
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6b/Hawaje-NoRedLine.jpg" width="400" alt="Spatial view of the state of Hawaii">
        <h6>Spatial view of the state of Hawaii.</h6>
